<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="keen-adj">keen <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kiːn/    美 /kiːn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>热衷的；渴望的</strong></h4>
<p>wanting to do sth (eager)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We <strong>were keen on</strong> going to picnic.
我们很想去野餐。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He's very <strong>keen to</strong> see his birthplace again.
他很想再去看一看自己出生的地方。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[非正式用语] (关心、兴趣等) 强烈的；浓烈的</strong></h4>
<p>very interested in sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a keen reader
热爱读书的人</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>have a keen interest in 
对…有强烈兴趣</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>am not very keen on</strong> detective stories.
我不太喜欢侦探小说。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-sharp">3.<strong>灵敏的；敏锐的 (sharp)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has <strong>a keen eye for</strong> (= is good at noticing) talent.
她慧眼识才。</p></div></div>